About:
  This test automation framework is based on Cucumber and Watir Webdriver tools.
  It implements the hybrid keyword-driven/page-element-object approach.

Prerequisites:
  1. Install all required gems (watir-webdriver, cucumber, syntax, mysql).
  2. To run the example test suite you should copy phplogin/ directory to the web server root folder.

Execution:
  Corresponding shell and batch files must be executed in order to run the tests against different browsers (Firefox, Chrome and Internet Explorer are currently supported).
  Using the default target all features and scenarios will be executed except those having @under_construction tag.

  You can also execute the selected features.
  cucumber features/some.feature - will execute the selected feature.

